<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1436,998,1851]" pageId="21" pageNumber="220">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,374,1070,1095]" pageId="21" pageNumber="220">
Notes on 
<typeStatus box="[312,374,1070,1095]" pageId="21" pageNumber="220">types</typeStatus>
</emphasis>
. Hesse (
<number box="[473,531,1070,1095]" pageId="21" pageNumber="220" value="1967.0">1967</number>
) based his description of 
<taxonomicName box="[825,968,1070,1095]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Platypygus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="220" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="natalensis">
<emphasis box="[825,968,1070,1095]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="220">P. natalensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on a single female 
<typeStatus box="[1193,1291,1070,1095]" pageId="21" pageNumber="220">holotype</typeStatus>
from Lilani, 
<collectingCountry box="[151,215,1106,1131]" name="South Africa" pageId="21" pageNumber="220">Natal</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[225,368,1106,1131]" name="South Africa" pageId="21" pageNumber="220">South Africa</collectingCountry>
deposited in NMSA. The 
<typeStatus box="[661,709,1107,1131]" pageId="21" pageNumber="220">type</typeStatus>
specimen was seen by NLE during his visit to the 
<collectingCountry box="[1271,1332,1106,1131]" name="South Africa" pageId="21" pageNumber="220">Natal</collectingCountry>
Museum in 
<number box="[180,236,1143,1167]" pageId="21" pageNumber="220" value="1990.0">1990</number>
and its condition of partially collapsed eyes due to air-drying and the apical one-fifth of the left wing being torn off were published in Evenhuis (
<number box="[570,631,1179,1203]" pageId="21" pageNumber="220" value="1993.0">1993</number>
). We re-examined the 
<typeStatus box="[883,981,1178,1203]" pageId="21" pageNumber="220">holotype</typeStatus>
during this study and there is no change to its condition (see 
<figureCitation box="[378,460,1214,1239]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="22.[151,249,1964,1986]" captionTargetBox="[174,1403,195,1928]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[174,1403,195,1934]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 13. Platypygus natalensis female holotype: a — lateral view, b — dorsal view, c — head (ventrolateral view), d — wing, e — detail view of vein Sc, f — head (anterior view)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/248562/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="220">
