<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="220" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1436,998,1851]" pageId="21" pageNumber="220">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,429,1250,1275]" pageId="21" pageNumber="220">Diagnostic features</emphasis>
. Face yellow; frons yellow becoming diffusely brown dorsally (
<figureCitation box="[1162,1243,1250,1275]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="22.[151,249,1964,1986]" captionTargetBox="[174,1403,195,1928]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[174,1403,195,1934]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 13. Platypygus natalensis female holotype: a — lateral view, b — dorsal view, c — head (ventrolateral view), d — wing, e — detail view of vein Sc, f — head (anterior view)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/248562/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="220">
Fig. 
<number box="[1215,1243,1250,1275]" pageId="21" pageNumber="220" value="13.0">13</number>
</figureCitation>
f); postgena with rounded posterior extension (
<figureCitation box="[488,572,1286,1311]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="22.[151,249,1964,1986]" captionTargetBox="[174,1403,195,1928]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[174,1403,195,1934]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 13. Platypygus natalensis female holotype: a — lateral view, b — dorsal view, c — head (ventrolateral view), d — wing, e — detail view of vein Sc, f — head (anterior view)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/248562/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="220">
Fig. 
<number box="[543,572,1287,1311]" pageId="21" pageNumber="220" value="13.0">13</number>
</figureCitation>
c), mentum yellow, concave ventrally; occiput black; ocellar triangle black (
<figureCitation box="[159,240,1322,1347]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="22.[151,249,1964,1986]" captionTargetBox="[174,1403,195,1928]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[174,1403,195,1934]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 13. Platypygus natalensis female holotype: a — lateral view, b — dorsal view, c — head (ventrolateral view), d — wing, e — detail view of vein Sc, f — head (anterior view)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/248562/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="220">
Fig. 
<number box="[212,240,1322,1347]" pageId="21" pageNumber="220" value="13.0">13</number>
</figureCitation>
f); antennae with scape and pedicel yellow, flagellomere black; mesonotum (
<figureCitation box="[1110,1190,1322,1347]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="22.[151,249,1964,1986]" captionTargetBox="[174,1403,195,1928]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[174,1403,195,1934]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 13. Platypygus natalensis female holotype: a — lateral view, b — dorsal view, c — head (ventrolateral view), d — wing, e — detail view of vein Sc, f — head (anterior view)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/248562/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="220">
Fig. 
<number box="[1163,1190,1322,1347]" pageId="21" pageNumber="220" value="13.0">13</number>
</figureCitation>
b) with a three brown stripes dorsally, medial stripe extending anteriorly to anterior margin of mesonotum, tapering posteriorly to rounded point before yellow prescutellar area; lateral stripe consisting of two parts thinly coalesced behind transverse suture; postpronotal lobes and postalar calli yellow; brown spot next to transverse suture; lateral margin of mesonotum yellow; scutellum yellow, lateral corners narrowly black; halter yellow; Sc fading toward tip and not reaching costa (
<figureCitation box="[327,408,1502,1527]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="22.[151,249,1964,1986]" captionTargetBox="[174,1403,195,1928]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[174,1403,195,1934]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 13. Platypygus natalensis female holotype: a — lateral view, b — dorsal view, c — head (ventrolateral view), d — wing, e — detail view of vein Sc, f — head (anterior view)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/248562/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="220">
Fig. 
<number box="[379,408,1503,1527]" pageId="21" pageNumber="220" value="13.0">13</number>
</figureCitation>
e); r-m slightly before middle of cell dm; cell br longer than cell bm (
<figureCitation box="[1180,1262,1502,1527]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="22.[151,249,1964,1986]" captionTargetBox="[174,1403,195,1928]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[174,1403,195,1934]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 13. Platypygus natalensis female holotype: a — lateral view, b — dorsal view, c — head (ventrolateral view), d — wing, e — detail view of vein Sc, f — head (anterior view)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/248562/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="220">
Fig. 
<number box="[1233,1262,1502,1527]" pageId="21" pageNumber="220" value="13.0">13</number>
</figureCitation>
d); legs orangeyellow except two last tarsal segments brownish black (
<figureCitation box="[775,856,1538,1563]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="22.[151,249,1964,1986]" captionTargetBox="[174,1403,195,1928]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[174,1403,195,1934]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 13. Platypygus natalensis female holotype: a — lateral view, b — dorsal view, c — head (ventrolateral view), d — wing, e — detail view of vein Sc, f — head (anterior view)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/248562/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="220">
Fig. 
<number box="[827,856,1539,1563]" pageId="21" pageNumber="220" value="13.0">13</number>
</figureCitation>
a).
</paragraph>
