<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="220" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1436,998,1851]" pageId="21" pageNumber="220">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,1610,1635]" pageId="21" pageNumber="220">Remarks</emphasis>
. The rather posterior extension of the postgena is unusual in 
<taxonomicName box="[1064,1188,1610,1635]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Platypygus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="220" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1064,1188,1610,1635]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="220">Platypygus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species and appears superficially to be more characteristic of 
<taxonomicName box="[623,757,1647,1670]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Cyrtisiopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="220" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[623,757,1647,1670]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="220">Cyrtisiopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, cell br is longer than cell bm, a major character separating 
<taxonomicName box="[276,410,1683,1706]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Cyrtisiopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="220" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[276,410,1683,1706]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="220">Cyrtisiopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName box="[485,609,1682,1707]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Platypygus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="220" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[485,609,1682,1707]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="220">Platypygus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. We were unable to dissect the unique female 
<typeStatus box="[1159,1257,1682,1707]" pageId="21" pageNumber="220">holotype</typeStatus>
and tentatively keep 
<taxonomicName box="[211,325,1718,1743]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Platypygus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="220" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="natalensis">
<emphasis box="[211,325,1718,1743]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="220">natalensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<taxonomicName box="[362,486,1718,1743]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Platypygus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="220" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[362,486,1718,1743]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="220">Platypygus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
awaiting further material from which to make genitalic dissections. Re-examination during this study of Namibian Platypyginae shows that the record of 
<taxonomicName box="[948,1092,1754,1779]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Platypygus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="220" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="natalensis">
<emphasis box="[948,1092,1754,1779]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="220">P. natalensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[1164,1261,1754,1779]" name="Namibia" pageId="21" pageNumber="220">Namibia</collectingCountry>
in Tschirnhaus (
<number box="[158,217,1791,1815]" pageId="21" pageNumber="220" value="2000.0">2000</number>
) was based on a misidentification of an aberrant specimen of 
<taxonomicName box="[927,1019,1790,1815]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Ahessea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="220" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[927,1019,1790,1815]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="220">Ahessea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, so we have removed 
<collectingCountry box="[1276,1372,1790,1815]" name="Namibia" pageId="21" pageNumber="220">Namibia</collectingCountry>
from the distributional range.
</paragraph>
